<section class="section exposing-a-myth" id="exposing-a-myth" aria-labelledby="exposing-a-myth-title">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__head">
      <h2 id="exposing-a-myth-title">What to Expect:</h2>
    </header>

    <div class="exposing-a-myth__card-wrap">
      <article class="exposing-a-myth__card" aria-labelledby="exposing-card-title">
        <header class="exposing-a-myth__card-banner">
          <h3 id="exposing-card-title" class="exposing-a-myth__card-title">Principles we'll cover:</h3>
          <p class="exposing-a-myth__card-sub"></p>
        </header>

        <ol class="exposing-a-myth__topics">
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 1</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Evil is moral, not a second god</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">Wickedness comes from human hearts and corrupt systems — not an immortal spirit rival ruling a rival kingdom.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 2</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">“Satan” is often a role, not a name-tag</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">“Adversary,” accuser, or obstacle — the language describes function and figure of speech, not proof of one cosmic villain being.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 3</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Genesis doesn’t hand you a rebel angel</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">The serpent story and later prophecy read in context don’t build the medieval devil-narrative people import into the text.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 4</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Jesus used dramatic picture-language</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">“The devil” in the Gospels fits prophetic and kingdom imagery — judgment, opposition, sin exposed — not a cosmic duel with another deity.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 5</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">One God — no co-eternal evil</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">A literal immortal Satan strains God’s sole sovereignty and how Scripture speaks of evil being confronted and ended at Christ’s return.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="exposing-a-myth__topic">
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-label">Principle 6</span>
            <span class="exposing-a-myth__topic-head">Sin and death are the real enemies</span>
            <p class="exposing-a-myth__topic-text">The gospel’s victory is over corruption and the grave — not winning an arm-wrestle against a rival evil god.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
